<dl id="n52157a"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n52" href="#n52157a">N52 (VI.B.42)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n52all.htm#n52157a"> 157(a)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> 6 dreamstates / 1) blood kindred / 2) meditation / 3) ideology <small>Blue</small></blockquote> <dd class="well"> <ul class="list-inline" id="n52157a"> <li>FW unlocated</li> </ul> <blockquote class="sources">The period betveen death and birth is divided into states analogous to the six solar months between Aries and Libra. The first state is called <i>The Vision of the Blood Kindred</i>, a vision of all those bound to us through <i>Husk</i> and <i>Passionate Body</i> &hellip; It is followed by the <i>Meditation</i> &hellip; In the third discarnate state it <font color="green">[?Husk]</font> may renounce the form of a man and take some shape from the social or religious tradition of its past life, symbolic or its condition <small> W.B. Yeats, <a name="WBYV1" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#WBYV1"><cite title="source">A Vision</cite></a> (Oct l937) 223-224</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
